### Error Boundaries with error.js

The `error.js` file creates a React Error Boundary that catches errors in its segment:

```jsx
'use client'; // Error boundaries must be Client Components

export default function Error({ error, reset }) {
  return (
    <div>
      <h2>Something went wrong!</h2>
      <p>{error.message}</p>
      <button onClick={() => reset()}>Try again</button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Error Component Props

- `error` — the Error object thrown
- `reset` — function to re-render the segment

### Nested Error Boundaries

`error.js` files wrap their segment and all children. Place them at different levels:

```
app/
  error.js            # Catches errors for the entire app
  dashboard/
    error.js          # Catches errors in /dashboard only
    page.js
  blog/
    [slug]/
      error.js        # Catches errors for individual blog posts
      page.js
```

### Global Error Handling

`global-error.js` is the fallback for the root layout:

```jsx
// app/global-error.js
'use client';

export default function GlobalError({ error, reset }) {
  return (
    <html>
      <body>
        <h2>Fatal error</h2>
        <button onClick={() => reset()}>Reload</button>
      </body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

### Not Found Pages

`not-found.js` handles 404 errors:

```jsx
// app/not-found.js
export default function NotFound() {
  return (
    <div>
      <h2>Page Not Found</h2>
      <p>The page you're looking for does not exist.</p>
      <a href="/">Go home</a>
    </div>
  );
}
```

Trigger 404 programmatically with `notFound()` from `next/navigation`:

```jsx
import { notFound } from 'next/navigation';

export default async function Post({ params }) {
  const post = await getPost(params.slug);

  if (!post) {
    notFound();
  }

  return <div>{post.title}</div>;
}
```

### Recovering from Errors

The `reset()` function attempts to re-render the segment. If the error was transient (network timeout), the page might recover successfully.

codeExample:
'use client';

export default function Error({ error, reset }) {
  return (
    <div className="error-container">
      <h2>Error: {error.message}</h2>
      <p>An unexpected error occurred. Please try again.</p>
      <button
        onClick={() => reset()}
        className="retry-button"
      >
        Try Again
      </button>
    </div>
  );
}

// Usage in page:
// app/dashboard/page.js
export default async function Dashboard() {
  const data = await fetchData(); // Errors caught by error.js
  return <div>{/* render data */}</div>;
}
